        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(claude-cli): update PermissionResult to match Claude Code 2.1.x schema",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nUpdate the `can_use_tool` permission response from the deprecated\n`{ behavior: \"allow\" }` to the Claude Code 2.1.x schema that expects\n`{ updatedInput: <record> }`.\n\n## Problem\n\nClaude Code 2.1.156 tightened the `PermissionResult` schema. OpenClaw\nreturned `{ behavior: \"allow\" }` which validates against neither branch\nof the new union, causing `ZodError` on every tool call.\n\nPinning Claude Code to 2.0.77 confirms the regression is on the\nOpenClaw bridge side.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nTwo locations returned the deprecated `{ behavior: \"allow\" }` shape:\n- `src/agents/cli-runner/claude-live-session.ts:879`\n- `src/agents/harness/native-hook-relay.ts:396`\n\n## Changes\n\n- `claude-live-session.ts` — return `{ updatedInput: request.input }`\n  instead of `{ behavior: \"allow\" }` for the allow path\n- `native-hook-relay.ts` — return `{ updatedInput: {} }` instead of\n  `{ behavior: \"allow\" }`; deny path unchanged\n\n## Related\n\nCloses #95171\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
